The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE DVD 

 (Landmark, Rs 1,250)

 The original fundraiser, before We Are The World and before Live Aid. This 1971 concert, organised by George Harrison at Madison Square Garden, saw performances by Eric Clapton, Ringo Starr, Billy Preston, Leon Rusell, Bob Dylan, Ravi Shankar and more to raise money for the flood-affected in Bangladesh.

 THE FEST

 (Max Mueller Bhavan, March 8-10, 6.30 pm)

 The package of three films from the German film studio UFA (Universum Film Aktiengesellschaft) features Joe May?s Asphalt, Douglas Sirk?s La Habanera and Helmut Kautner?s Under the Bridges.

 THE DISPLAY 

 (Artisana, March 10-19, 10 am-7.30 pm)

 The spring collection exhibition, organised by Crafts Council of India , showcases traditional textiles like Chanderi, Ikkat, Maheswari, Jamdani, Bomkai and cotton saris from Tamil Nadu, among others.




